ough%20denial%20of%20advanced%20technology%20and%20by%20pressuring%20the%20Europeans%20to%20do%20so%20too.%20A%20change%20of%20posture%20away%20from%20wolf-warrior%20diplomacy%20towards%20a%20more%20friendly%20demeanour%20is%20a%20tactical%20move%20by%20Xi%20Jinping.%20The%20fundamentals%20of%20China's%20internal%20and%20external%20policies%20remain%20unchanged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20continues%20to%20threaten%20Taiwan%20with%20military%20manoeuvres.%20It%20is%20also%20not%20backing%20off%20from%20its%20violations%20of%20the%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20Philippines%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20despite%20the%20strengthening%20of%20its%20defence%20ties%20with%20the%20US.%20Its%20economic%20strategy%20is%20still%20centred%20around%20controlling%20select%20critical%20raw%20materials%20and%20technologies%2C%20which%20ensures%20that%20other%20countries%20remain%20dependent%20on%20it.%20China%20also%20uses%20its%20massive%20industrial%20capacity%20to%20overproduce%20products%20and%20then%20dump%20them%20in%20international%20markets%20to%20knock%20out%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fin-beijing-antony-blinken-confronts-china-over-powering-russias-war-5530682%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0In%20Beijing%2C%20Antony%20Blinken%20Confronts%20China%20Over%20%26quot%3BPowering%26quot%3B%20Russia's%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Europe%20do%20not%20know%20how%20to%20control%20this%20manufacturing%20juggernaut.%20America%20cannot%20impose%20on%20China%20something%20akin%20to%20the%20Plaza%20Accord%2C%20which%20it%20had%20used%20with%20Japan%20in%201985.%20That's%20because%20unlike%20Japan%2C%20China%20does%20not%20depend%20on%20the%20US%20for%20its%20security.%20The%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20(WTO)%2C%20too%2C%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20control%20China.%20The%20absurdity%20is%20that%20China%20still%20identifies%20itself%20as%20a%20developing%20country%20in%20the%20trade%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20'Decoupling'%20To%20'De-Risking'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20underlined%20the%20risks%20of%20over-dependence%20on%20China%20in%20some%20critical%20areas%2C%20leading%20to%20talk%20about%20decoupling%20from%20it%20and%20developing%20alternative%2C%20resilient%20and%20more%20trustworthy%20supply%20chains.%20On-shoring%20production%2C%20that%20is%2C%20reviving%20domestic%20manufacturing%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20US%2C%20which%20lost%20a%20large%20part%20of%20its%20manufacturing%20base%20as%20companies%20shifted%20production%20facilities%20to%20lower-cost%20China%2C%20became%20a%20pressing%20post-pandemic%20strategy.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20Trump%20had%20already%20initiated%20this%20policy%20objective%20as%20part%20of%20the%20'America%20First'%20and%20'Make%20America%20Great%20Again'%20pitches.%20The%20US%20is%20now%20determined%20to%20develop%20its%20own%20semiconductor%20industry%20and%20green%20energy%20framework%2C%20for%20which%20it%20is%20giving%20incentives%20under%20the%20Chips%20Act%20and%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20%26quot%3Bdecoupling%26quot%3B%20the%20US%20economy%20from%20China's%20has%20now%20been%20abandoned.%20The%20talk%20now%20is%20of%20%26quot%3Bde-risking%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20means%20reducing%20dependency%20in%20select%20critical%20areas.%20The%20American%20corporate%20sector%20has%20large%20stakes%20in%20the%20Chinese%20market%2C%20with%20some%20entities%20facing%20the%20risk%20of%20collapse%20if%20they%20withdraw%20from%20it.%20There's%20a%20gap%20between%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20security%20concerns%20of%20the%20US%20government%20over%20China's%20emergence%20as%20a%20powerful%20rival%20and%20the%20trade%20and%20financial%20interests%20of%20US%20corporations%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS's%20Internal%20Dynamics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20US%20is%20developing%20an%20industrial%20policy%2C%20its%20system%20does%20not%20allow%20state%20control%20over%20market%20decisions%20of%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20more%20so%20because%20it%20has%20spent%20years%20propagating%20the%20market%20economy%20as%20a%20universal%20solution%20to%20economic%20growth%2C%20including%20through%20the%20World%20Bank%20and%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF).%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20bipartisan%20Congressional%20committees%20that%20are%20examining%20the%20China%20threat%20has%20been%20that%20the%20corporate%20representatives%20are%20not%20as%20sensitive%20to%20this%20threat%20as%20the%20security%20establishment%20is.%20This%20is%20indicated%20by%20the%20fawning%20remarks%20of%20the%2030%20top%20American%20CEOs%20after%20their%20meeting%20with%20Xi%20Jinping%20in%20late%20March%20this%20year%2C%20where%20they%20were%20soft-soaped%20by%20the%20Chinese%20president.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fantony-blinken-buys-taylor-swift-album-from-beijing-record-store-5531389%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Antony%20Blinken%20Buys%20Taylor%20Swift%20Album%20From%20Beijing%20Record%20Store%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20see%20no%20difference%20in%20%26quot%3Bdecoupling%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bde-risking%26quot%3B%20as%20concepts%20because%20they%20see%20it%20as%20a%20US%20strategy%20to%20impede%20China's%20technological%20progress%20by%20seeking%20to%20deny%20it%20access%20to%20the%20most%20advanced%20Western%20technologies.%20While%20concerned%20about%20US%20restrictions%20and%20pressure%20on%20Europe%20to%20follow%20suit%2C%20the%20Chinese%20are%20also%20confident%20that%20their%20grip%20on%20solar%20panel%20and%20electrical%20vehicle%20technologies%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20compels%20the%20West%20to%20recognise%20and%20accommodate%20the%20reality.%20It%20appears%20that%20Chinese%20business%20companies%20are%20systematically%20penetrating%20the%20European%20market%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20discourse%20of%20European%20leaders%20about%20unfair%20competition%2C%20state%20subsidies%20and%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20the%20Chinese%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Contradictory%20Policy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20strategy%20towards%20China%20seems%20contradictory.%20China%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20pacing%20threat%20beyond%20the%20situation%20in%20the%20Western%20Pacific%20and%20its%20technological%20containment%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20preferred%20policy%20choice.%20And%20yet%2C%20there%20is%20a%20desire%20to%20have%20a%20constructive%20dialogue%20with%20it%20to%20establish%20a%20degree%20of%20stability%20in%20ties%2C%20some%20%26quot%3Bguard%20rails%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20US%20says%2C%20with%20a%20particular%20focus%20on%20resuming%20dialogue%20at%20the%20military%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20the%20US%20can%20square%20this%20circle%2C%20with%20a%20China%20that%20is%20growing%20more%20nationalistic%20and%20increasingly%20stronger%20militarily%20and%20has%20a%20technology%20base%20in%20some%20critical%20areas%20that%20is%20more%20advanced%20than%20that%20of%20the%20West%2C%20is%20not%20evident.%20Beijing%20is%20confident%20of%20its%20growing%20clout%20in%20international%20relations%20and%20is%20already%20exercising%20influence%20in%20areas%20where%20the%20US%20was%20hitherto%20the%20dominant%20force%2C%20including%20in%20the%20United%20Nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlinken%20announced%20in%20advance%20that%20he%20would%20clamp%20down%20on%20China%20over%20some%20issues%20of%20US%20concern%20-%20namely%2C%20its%20support%20for%20Russia's%20war%20against%20Ukraine%20-%20and%20may%20even%20go%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20introducing%20sanctions%20in%20case%20Beijing%20was%20recalcitrant.%20Though%20China%20did%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20supplying%20Russia%20with%20lethal%20assistance%2C%20Blinken%20noted%20that%20it%20was%20providing%20machine%20tools%2C%20microelectronics%20and%20other%20dual-use%20items%20that%20made%20it%20the%20%26quot%3Btop%20supplier%26quot%3B%20for%20Russia's%20defence%20industrial%20base.%20Russia%2C%20he%20believed%2C%20would%20struggle%20to%20sustain%20its%20assault%20on%20Ukraine%20without%20China's%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuying%20Time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20was%20utilised%20too%20to%20send%20a%20tough%20message%20to%20China%20in%20advance%2C%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%20reporting%20that%20Blinken%20would%20tell%20Wang%20Yi%20that%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20were%20becoming%20increasingly%20impatient%20with%20Beijing's%20refusal%20to%20stop%20providing%20Moscow%20with%20everything%20from%20chips%20to%20cruise%20missiles%20engines%20so%20as%20to%20help%20it%20build%20its%20industrial%20base%2C%20and%20that%20the%20US%20was%20considering%20sanctions%20on%20Chinese%20financial%20institutions%20and%20other%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20rather%20unclear%20background%20that%20Blinken%20visited%20China%20late%20last%20month%20-%20%26quot%3Bon%20invitation%26quot%3B%2C%20%C2%A0to%20distinguish%20it%20from%20other%20visits%20such%20as%20that%20by%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Yellen%20-%20and%20met%20his%20own%20counterpart%20as%20well%20as%20Xi%20Jinping.%20The%20visit%20did%20not%20achieve%20any%20breakthroughs.%20US-China%20relations%20are%20now%20in%20a%20holding%20pattern%2C%20with%20both%20buying%20time%20-%20the%20US%20to%20regain%20the%20strengths%20it%20has%20lost%2C%20and%20China%20to%20gain%20strengths%20to%20realise%20its%20aspirations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2