y%20to%20see%20why.%20Rising%20inflation%2C%20spiking%20consumer%20prices%2C%20supply-chain%20issues%2C%20instability%20in%20the%20global%20market%2C%20and%20labor%20shortages%20all%20have%20many%20financial%20experts%20saying%20that%20another%20recession%20is%20around%20the%20corner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20financial%20planner%2C%20I%20often%20get%20asked%20when%20the%20next%20recession%20is%20coming.%20While%20I%20can't%20exactly%20predict%20when%20the%20economy%20may%20take%20a%20turn%20for%20the%20worse%2C%20I%20can%20offer%20some%20good%20news%3A%20We're%20currently%20not%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Frecession-vs-depression%5C%22%3Erecession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20yet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20now%20is%20the%20best%20possible%20time%20to%20prepare%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20my%20tips%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20the%20tides%20and%20recession-proof%20your%20cash.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Think%20about%20where%20to%20cut%20back%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20things%20have%20gotten%20more%20expensive%20recently%20%E2%80%94%20gas%2C%20food%2C%20cars%2C%20furniture%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20now's%20a%20great%20time%20to%20revisit%20your%20budget%20and%20identify%20some%20areas%20to%20cut%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20huge%20fan%20of%20using%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20a%20living%2C%20breathing%20record%20that%20can%20be%20revised%20and%20changed%20as%20your%20needs%20change.%20The%20easiest%20items%20to%20scrap%20are%20services%20or%20purchases%20you%20can%20live%20without%20%E2%80%94%20think%20dinners%20out%2C%20streaming%20services%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20need%20to%20go%20and%20cut%20out%20all%20the%20things%20that%20bring%20you%20joy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeciding%20if%20something%20is%20a%20need%20or%20a%20want%20isn't%20always%20black%20and%20white.%20Some%20things%20that%20may%20seem%20non-essential%20to%20some%20people%2C%20like%20a%20gym%20membership%2C%20others%20can't%20live%20without.%20It's%20all%20about%20weighing%20your%20current%20priorities%20with%20your%20long-term%20goals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Start%20building%20your%20rainy-day%20reserves%2C%20if%20you%20haven't%20already%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecession%20or%20not%2C%20you%20should%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20savings%20help%20you%20avoid%20borrowing%20money%20to%20cover%20unforeseen%20costs%20like%20repairs%2C%20medical%20treatments%2C%20or%20job%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20just%20starting%20out%2C%20I%20recommend%20having%20around%20six%20months'%20worth%20of%20expenses%2C%20including%20the%20amounts%20you%20spend%20on%20necessary%20items%20like%20rent%2C%20utilities%2C%20and%20groceries.%20That%20number%20may%20sound%20high%20at%20first%2C%20but%20small%20contributions%20over%20time%20can%20build%20those%20savings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20want%20to%20store%20your%20emergency%20money%20in%20a%20liquid%20account%20(like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E)%20to%20easily%20access%20it%20when%20you%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20Exclusive%20Savings%20with%20Raisin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Open%20a%20no-fee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3ERaisin%3C%2Fa%3E%20account%20in%20minutes%20and%20spread%20your%20savings%20across%20an%20exclusive%20network%20of%20over%2030%20FDIC-insured%20banks%20and%20NCUA-insured%20credit%20unions.%20Earn%20top%20savings%20rates%20and%20manage%20it%20all%20with%20a%20single%20secure%20login.%20%3Cspan%3EView%20offers%20and%20start%20saving%20today%20%C2%BB%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Pay%20off%20high-interest%20debt%20ASAP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20thing%20you%20want%20to%20deal%20with%20during%20a%20recession%20is%20high-interest%20debt%20weighing%20you%20down.%20Credit-card%20debt%20should%20be%20the%20first%20to%20go.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interest%20rate%20determined%20by%20the%20Fed%20influences%20short-term%20lending%20like%20credit%20cards.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-credit-card-interest-rate%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20interest%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20go%20up%20even%20higher%2C%20causing%20you%20to%20pay%20hundreds%20(or%20thousands)%20in%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20pay%20off%20your%20debt%2C%20you'll%20have%20room%20in%20your%20budget%20to%20put%20towards%20other%20things%2C%20like%20growing%20your%20emergency%20fund%20or%20making%20up%20for%20rising%20consumer%20prices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Think%20about%20your%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecessions%20historically%20go%20hand-in-hand%20with%20higher%20unemployment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20preparing%20your%20career%20for%20the%20next%20downturn%20is%20essential.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow's%20a%20great%20time%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20your%20network%20and%20continue%20to%20maintain%20connections%20with%20others%20in%20your%20field.%20Typically%2C%20higher%20education%20comes%20with%20lower%20rates%20of%20unemployment%20%E2%80%94%20so%20if%20you've%20been%20thinking%20about%20going%20back%20to%20school%2C%20now%20may%20be%20the%20time.%20Adding%20new%20skills%20or%20bolstering%20your%20current%20ones%20could%20give%20you%20an%20edge%20in%20a%20future%2C%20tighter%20job%20market.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20sure%20to%20weigh%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20potentially%20forgoing%20a%20salary%20or%20taking%20on%20student%20loan%20debt%20to%20earn%20your%20degree.%20I%20would%20also%20recommend%20being%20practical%20about%20what%20industry%20you're%20considering.%20No%20job%20is%20completely%20protected%20from%20recessions%2C%20but%20certain%20industries%20are%20safer%20from%20cuts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Keep%20calm%20and%20carry%20on%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecessions%20can%20be%20an%20emotional%20and%20stressful%20time%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20your%20investments.%20Watching%20your%20portfolio%20fall%20into%20the%20red%20can%20be%20worrisome%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20to%20avoid%20making%20a%20knee-jerk%20reaction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanging%20your%20investment%20strategy%20could%20hurt%20you%20in%20the%20long%20run%20%E2%80%94%20the%20market%20often%20grows%20in%20the%20long%20term%20and%20behaves%20in%20ways%20you%20may%20not%20expect.%20Case%20in%20point%3A%20After%20falling%20more%20than%2030%25%20in%20March%202020%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20had%20a%20full%20rebound%20(and%20then%20some!).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20really%20want%20to%20take%20action%20before%20any%20future%20recession%2C%20I%20would%20recommend%20simply%20revisiting%20and%20rebalancing%20some%20of%20your%20investments.%20Having%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-diversification%5C%22%3Ediversified%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20minimize%20your%20losses%20during%20a%20volatile%20market.%20Remember%3A%20If%20you%20have%20an%20already-diversified%20portfolio%2C%20doubling%20down%20on%20your%20plan%20and%20focusing%20on%20the%20long%20term%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20things%20you%20can%20do%20for%20your%20money.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20recession%20can%20be%20anxiety-producing.%20But%20making%20a%20plan%20beforehand%20and%20taking%20the%20steps%20to%20prepare%20yourself%20can%20help%20you%20feel%20more%20in%20control%20of%20your%20situation%20and%20reduce%20some%20of%20your%20stress.%20To%20me%2C%20there's%20never%20a%20bad%20time%20to%20revisit%20your%20financial%20situation%20%E2%80%94%20so%20if%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20sign%2C%20now's%20the%20time%20to%20start!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprepare-money-for-recession-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715291341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F628652c90fdb180018cc26c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprepare-money-for-recession-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Financial%20planner%20Hanna%20Horvath%20says%20bulking%20up%20your%20emergency%20fund%20and%20taking%20cou