2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-403b%5C%22%3E403(b)%3C%2Fa%3E%20retirement%20account%2C%20I%20did%20so.%20It's%20always%20easier%20to%20put%20money%20into%20investments%20before%20you%20start%20seeing%20it%20in%20your%20paycheck%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20I%20could%20make%20investing%20a%20priority%20before%20spending%20that%20money%20on%20things%20that%20I%20didn't%20necessarily%20want%20or%20need.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20became%20eligible%20to%20open%20a%20403(b)%2C%20another%20teacher%20within%20the%20school%20district%20contacted%20me%20to%20help%20me%20set%20it%20up.%20He%20was%20registered%20through%20the%20education%20services%20company%20that%20our%20district%20used%2C%20but%20looking%20back%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20he%20gave%20me%20enough%20information%20to%20decide%20how%20to%20invest%20my%20money%20wisely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20recommended%20some%20investment%20funds%20that%20were%20aligned%20with%20my%20risk%20tolerance%20and%20length%20of%20investing%2C%20so%20I%20went%20with%20his%20suggestions.%20However%2C%20I%20was%20unaware%20of%20the%20fees%20and%20performance%20associated%20with%20these%20funds.%20As%20I%20became%20more%20interested%20in%20personal%20finance%20and%20started%20educating%20myself%20more%20on%20investments%2C%20I%20started%20to%20realize%20the%20mistakes%20I'd%20make.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20mutual%20fund%20fees%20I%20was%20paying%20were%20excessive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20left%20teaching%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20in%20financial%20services%2C%20I%20couldn't%20believe%20how%20high%20some%20of%20the%20fees%20were%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-invest-in-mutual-funds%5C%22%3Emutual%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20403(b)%2C%20and%20was%20even%20more%20shocked%20at%20how%20high%20the%20fees%20ended%20up%20being%20once%20you%20added%20in%20management%20and%20other%20annual%20fees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Walsh%2C%20a%20financial%20planner%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsofi-bank-review%5C%22%3ESoFi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20explained%20to%20me%20that%20403(b)%20plans%20in%20the%20K-12%20space%20are%20historically%20known%20for%20higher%20fees%20because%20they%20sometimes%20contain%20variable%20annuity%20options.%20Sometimes%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20fees%20on%20these%20plans%20can%20be%20between%202%25%20and%203%25%20because%20of%20the%20annuities.%20(By%20comparison%2C%20an%20%26quot%3Bexpensive%26quot%3B%20401(k)%20fee%20is%20around%202%25.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20wasn't%20in%20an%20annuity%20plan%20myself%2C%20I%20now%20know%20that%20many%20individuals%20get%20talked%20into%20investing%20in%20an%20annuity%20without%20understanding%20how%20they%20operate%20and%20what%20their%20fee%20structure%20looks%20like.%20Even%20without%20an%20annuity%20plan%2C%20though%2C%20I%20know%20the%20fees%20I%20was%20paying%20in%20my%20403(b)%20were%20considerably%20higher%20than%20the%20fees%20I%20now%20pay%20in%20my%20self-managed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-invest-in-index-funds%5C%22%3Eindex%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20portfolio.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EWealthfront%20is%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-robo-advisors%5C%22%3Ebest%20robo-advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20investing%20options%20for%20low-cost%20automated%20or%20self-managed%20portfolios.%20Read%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwealthfront-review%5C%22%3EWealthfront%20investing%20review%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20your%20employer-sponsored%20retirement%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20you%20have%20limited%20choices%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20your%20employer-sponsored%20retirement%20plan%2C%20it's%20still%20important%20to%20do%20your%20own%20research%20before%20blindly%20putting%20your%20money%20into%20investments%20chosen%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20if%20that%20advisor%20is%20going%20to%20make%20a%20commission%20off%20of%20your%20choices%2C%20as%20that%20can%20dictate%20what%20investments%20they%20recommend%20to%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBobby%20Glotfelty%2C%20an%20investment%20advisor%20representative%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.betterment.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBetterment%20for%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20the%20following%20recommendations%20for%20choosing%20investments%20and%20decreasing%20fees%20within%20your%20403(b)%20plan%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Look%20for%20low-cost%20funds.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20He%20recommends%20index%20funds%20as%20well%20as%20passively%20managed%20mutual%20funds%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-etf%5C%22%3Eexchange-traded%20funds%20(ETFs)%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20If%20available%20in%20your%20plan%2C%20invest%20in%20a%20target-date%20fund.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20These%20are%20generally%20low-cost%2C%20allow%20for%20proper%20diversification%2C%20and%20will%20decrease%20risk%20over%20time%20as%20you%20approach%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Avoid%20actively%20managed%20mutual%20funds%20and%20annuities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20since%20these%20types%20of%20investments%20are%20generally%20subject%20to%20very%20high%20fund%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Before%20you%20join%20a%20403(b)%20plan%2C%20know%20that%20costly%20403(b)%20fees%20can%20significantly%20reduce%20your%20savings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20over%20the%20course%20of%20your%20career%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20by%20hundreds%20